reviews.text: Really nice Mexican food with reasonable price! Highly recommend the soup, guacamole and tacos especially the taco combo! A surprising fusion by mixing up western and Japanese style. Only if the servers can be a little bit more friendly it would be even better;)
Amber the manager of this place is the reason I keep going back. The guy remembers everyone that comes in. The food is also really good! Great happy hour as well
Great dishes, great service and most importantly drinks that is perfectly mixed and matched. A really great place to chill out with friends.
Good portion for good price. Atmosphere is alright and it's busy during the weekends

Great tacos! We ordered 3 each of their main tacos - the lobster taco was delicious but the scallop taco could’ve done with another scallop rather than just one piece of scallop. I wish the tacos came with slices of lime in case we wanted to squeeze lime over the tacos prior to eating them. 
The corn chips with salsa was spicy nice and the guacamole is a must! Shame the serving of the guacamole was slightly on the small side. 
Drinks were really nice but wish they came before we got the tacos. Instead they came just before we were finishing our 3rd taco. 
To finish of our meal, we got the deep fried ice cream which was amazing to watch when fired up (as per image). The churros was nice but wish the chocolate served with it was better.

シーシャ（水タバコ）を吸いたくて1階のバーに行った所、シーシャは3階だと言われ上がってみるとメキシコレストランでした。
食事用のメニューも色々ありましたが、お酒を飲みながらシーシャを楽しんでいる人がほとんどでした。
お店の内装は非常に簡素でチープな印象です。愛想の悪い女性店員もいましたが、店のサービス自体はそれほど悪くありません。シーシャの炭も無料で交換してくれます。

reviews.text: The quality of food is simply amazing. One of the best in HK

In Hong Kong for business and so far all my dinning experiences have been great until I decided to try Hanabi. I called earlier during the day to make a reservation and asked for sushi bar availability. I arrived at the restaurant exactly when my reservations was. Despite having a couple of single empty seats at the bar, the host toyally refused to sit me at the bar and instead was adamant in me sitting at a table. I pointed out two single chairs that were open but she was not having it. Strange situation with a terrible host.
Nice place and nice food

Only 6 customers on a Friday night. Sadly 1 last was drunk and ruined the mood of the night.  The overall food quality was nice, but nothing extraordinary. These days omakase has been so overpriced in general in Hong Kong that I can't say whether it's ok for the price or not. Service was good and attentive

The lace looks ok and the stuff are really nice but the prices are crazy! You cannot buy separate dishes - just set combinations I think the cheapest is 600 hkd 😒 and there are sets like 1500 hkd... Consider that.
